{%- comment -%}
  The article's byline. ONE source of truth — the Journal cards, the blog grid and the article
  page all render through this, so the name can never disagree between them.

  Order of precedence:
    1. the `custom.author` metafield on the article  (an editor said so — always wins)
    2. otherwise article.author, Shopify's own field

  The metafield exists because Shopify's native author is a STAFF ACCOUNT name — the list of
  store users, not a byline. A guest writer or a pen name cannot be made a staff account, so
  the editor needs a field Shopify does not limit. The fallback keeps every article that has
  no override rendering exactly what it rendered before.

  Outputs the bare name, nothing else. The caller supplies the "By" prefix, so wording stays
  in the section's settings where a merchant can translate it.

  @param {object} article - a Shopify article
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign byline = article.metafields.custom.author.value | default: article.author
  echo byline
-%}
